-- Battistero Plans $65 Million Romania Investment, Adevarul Says
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-09-19T06:22:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-19/battistero-plans-65-million-romania-investment-adevarul-says.html
Battistero SpA, a privately owned
Italian company, plans to invest 50 million euros ($65 million)
in a factory in  Romania ,  Adevarul  newspaper reported today,
citing the company’s owner.  The Parma-based cake producer plans to build the factory
near the central Romanian city of Cluj-Napoca and start making
panettone, a sweet bread studded with raisins, and other cakes
beginning in September 2013, Felice Moretti, Battistero’s owner
said, according to Adevarul.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  